LogicalTable.name: F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples
LogicalTable.Description: This logical table contains metrics that always return value at a particular level within a dimension. Eg:- Revenue at Month level, Billed Qtry at Year level, Booked Amt for all Products etc. All metrics in this table are logical calculations based on physically mapped metrics from F0 Rev Base Measures and F1 Inv Base Measures.

LogicalColumn.name: 121 ---- Dynamic Time Level ---------------------
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Header object, dummy not to be used in any queries

LogicalColumn.name: 121 Period Ago Rev
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Returns data as of previous month vs. month selected in the query.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: AGO("01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue", 1)

LogicalColumn.name: 122 Rev Var to Period Ago
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Value change to last month

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue" - "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."121 Period Ago Rev"

LogicalColumn.name: 123 Rev Pct Var to Period Ago
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Average % change to last month value

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."122 Rev Var to Period Ago" / "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."121 Period Ago Rev" * 100

LogicalColumn.name: 125 N Period Agos Rev
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Returns data as of 2 months before month selected in the query.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: AGO("01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue", VALUEOF(NQ_SESSION."N_AGO_PERIODS"))

LogicalColumn.name: 126 Rev Pct Var to N Period Ago
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Average % change to last month value

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: (("01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue" / "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."125 N Period Agos Rev" ) -1) *100

Expr.name: Expr

LogicalColumn.name: 131 Rev Var to Qtr Ago
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.

LogicalColumn.name: 132 Rev Pct Var to Qtr Ago
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Percent difference of the value of the metric in the current period with the value of the metric in the same period the previous quarter / Value of the metric in the same period of the previous quarter

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."131 Rev Var to Qtr Ago" / "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."128 Qtr Ago Rev (Fix Time Lvl)" * 100

LogicalColumn.name: 133 Rev QAgo Compounded Yrly Gwth
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- % variation to last quarter expressed in a compounded yearly % growth rate.

Expr.name: Expr

LogicalColumn.name: 135 Qtr To Dt Rev Sum
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Sums all the values from the first day of the quarter to the current period

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: TODATE("01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue", "01 - Sample App"."H0 Time"."Quarter")

LogicalColumn.name: 136 Qtr Ago QTD Rev sum
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Quarter Ago Quarter-To-Date Value for the same period. For the same period in the previous quarter, it returns the sum of all the values from the first day of the quarter to that period.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: TODATE("01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."128 Qtr Ago Rev (Fix Time Lvl)", "01 - Sample App"."H0 Time"."Quarter")

LogicalColumn.name: 137 QTD Rev Pct Var to Qago QTD
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Average % change of Quarter to date current value to last Quarter quarter to date value

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: ("01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."135 Qtr To Dt Rev Sum" / "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."136 Qtr Ago QTD Rev sum" - 1) * 100

LogicalColumn.name: 144 ======== Rolling Measures ========
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Header object, dummy not to be used in any queries

LogicalColumn.name: 144 ---- Alias Based Modelling -------
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Header object, dummy not to be used in any queries

LogicalColumn.name: 144 Trailing N Mth Rev (Alias Based)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Rolling 3 months sum as of selected month : sum of current month plus previous two months value. For January, it gives the value of January plus December and November of the previous year

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: FILTER("01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."117 Unbound Rolling Rev (Alias Based)" USING "01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."X10 Dim Julian Mth Number" - "01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."X11 Fact Julian Mth Number" < VALUEOF(NQ_SESSION."N_TRAIL_PAST_MTHS"))

LogicalColumn.name: 145 Trailing N Mth Rev Daily Avg
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Daily average over Rolling 3 months period : Rolling 3 months sum as of selected month divided by number of days in R3M period.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."144 Trailing N Mth Rev (Alias Based)" / ( VALUEOF(NQ_SESSION."N_TRAIL_PAST_MTHS") * 30.4d)

LogicalColumn.name: 146 Trailing N Mth Rev Mthly Avg
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Monthly average over Rolling 3 months period : Rolling 3 months sum as of selected month divided by 3

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."144 Trailing N Mth Rev (Alias Based)" / VALUEOF(NQ_SESSION."N_TRAIL_PAST_MTHS")

LogicalColumn.name: 150 ======== Level Based Measures ========
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Header object, dummy not to be used in any queries

LogicalColumn.name: 150 ---- Time Level Based ---------
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Header object, dummy not to be used in any queries

LogicalColumn.name: 150 Rev (Full Mth Sum)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Sum of the metric value for the full month. This aggregation is always calculated at the month level.. For example, when viewed against Week level, it shows the same total month's value for all the weeks in that month.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue"

LogicalColumn.name: 151 Rev (Full Qtr Sum)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Sum of the metric value for the full quarter. This aggregation is always calculated at the quarter level. When viewed against Month or Week level, it shows the quarter's value for all the weeks and months in that quarter.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue"

LogicalColumn.name: 152 Rev (Full Year Sum)
LogicalColumn.Description:

- Sum of the metric value for the full year. This aggregation is always calculated at the year level. When viewed against quarter, month or week level, it shows the year's value for all the quarters, month, and weeks in that year.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue"

LogicalColumn.name: 153 Rev (Mago Full Mth Sum)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Full month's value of the metric for the previous month. This aggregation is always calculated at the month level. For example, when viewed against Week level, it shows the same total month's value for all the weeks in that month.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."127 Mth Ago Rev (Fix Time Lvl)"

LogicalColumn.name: 154 Rev (Yago Full Mth Sum)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Full month's value of the metric for the same month in the previous year. This aggregation is always calculated at the year level. For example, when viewed against Week level, it shows the same total month's value for all the weeks in that month.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: AGO("01 - Sample App"."F0 Sales Base Measures"."1- Revenue", "01 - Sample App"."H0 Time"."Month", 12)

LogicalColumn.name: 155 Rev (Yago Full Year Sum)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- Full year's value of the metric for the previous year. This aggregation is always calculated at the year level

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F5 Time Series and Level Based Examples"."129 Year Ago Rev (Fix Time Lvl)"

LogicalColumn.name: 954 ---- Time Spans Var---------------------
LogicalColumn.Description: Help : Header object, dummy not to be used in any queries

LogicalColumn.name: 954 FTE Headcount (Value Var)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- For any time interval specified in the query row, this aggregation returns the difference between value at beginning of the interval and value at end of the interval. The values at beginning and end date that make up the variation can be displayed by adding aggregation objects Fst oT and Last oT. Info about beginning date and end date for each row are available with time facts objects : First Time Day Dt and Last Time Day Dt. For example, if a query is filtered for a quarter, this will show the value variation between first and last day of the quarter. If the query objects are at week level, This aggregation will returns for each row (week level) the value of the last day of each week minus value of the first day in that week.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: "01 - Sample App"."F4 Headcount Base Measures"."9- Full Time Empl (End Period)" - "01 - Sample App"."F4 Headcount Base Measures"."9- Full Time Empl (Beg Period)"

LogicalColumn.name: 955 FTE Headcount (Pct Var)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- This aggregation converts the Value Var aggregation metric into a percentage variation to first value (Value Var / initial value *100)

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: ("01 - Sample App"."F4 Headcount Base Measures"."9- Full Time Empl (End Period)" - "01 - Sample App"."F4 Headcount Base Measures"."9- Full Time Empl (Beg Period)" ) / "01 - Sample App"."F4 Headcount Base Measures"."9- Full Time Empl (Beg Period)" * 100

LogicalColumn.name: 956 FTE Headcount (Cmpd Yrly Gwth)
LogicalColumn.Description:
Help : Revenue data. Sources from Dollars physical column in FactsRev table joining to time using Billed time.
- For any time interval specified in the query row, this aggregation returns the difference between value at beginning of the interval and value at end of the interval. The values at beginning and end date that make up the variation can be displayed by adding aggregation objects Fst oT and Last oT. Info about beginning date and end date for each row are available with time facts objects : First Time Day Dt and Last Time Day Dt. For example, if a query is filtered for a quarter, this will show the value variation between first and last day of the quarter. If the query objects are at week level, This aggregation will returns for each row (week level) the value of the last day of each week minus value of the first day in that week.

Expr.name: Expr
Expr.ExprTextDesc: ( POWER( "01 - Sample App"."F4 Headcount Base Measures"."9- Full Time Empl (End Period)" / "01 - Sample App"."F4 Headcount Base Measures"."9- Full Time Empl (Beg Period)" , (12/ "01 - Sample App"."F90 Time Facts"."T64 # of Months" )) - 1) * 100
